text: Okanogan County is a county in the U.S. state of Washington. At the 2020 census, 42,104 people lived there. The county seat is Okanogan, while the largest city is Omak. Its area is the largest in the state. ==References== Category:1888 establishments in the United States Category:1880s establishments in Washington (state) Category:Washington (state) counties
